00:35:31.556 --> 00:35:33.710
will prevent all these things
from happening.

00:35:33.710 --> 00:35:36.409
Now, I'm ready to state that
law.

00:35:36.409 --> 00:35:39.934
This is the third law--I mean,
the Second Law of

00:35:39.934 --> 00:35:42.321
Thermodynamics.
Carnot said it one way,

00:35:42.321 --> 00:35:44.446
but I'm going to say it in a
way that's very,

00:35:44.446 --> 00:35:47.194
very general.
The Second Law of

00:35:47.194 --> 00:35:54.397
Thermodynamics says ∆S
for the universe is either zero

00:35:54.397 --> 00:35:57.305
or positive.
There you have it,

00:35:57.305 --> 00:36:00.035
that's the great law.
The law says,

00:36:00.035 --> 00:36:04.555
take any process,
if at the end of the process

00:36:04.555 --> 00:36:10.180
the entropy of the universe is
bigger than it was before,

00:36:10.180 --> 00:36:14.212
that will happen.
If the entropy of the universe

00:36:14.212 --> 00:36:17.309
is smaller than it was before,
it will not happen.

00:36:17.309 --> 00:36:20.997
Now, we have to make sure that
this law has anything whatsoever

00:36:20.997 --> 00:36:24.684
to do with all the other things
we have studied and I will show

00:36:24.684 --> 00:36:26.326
you;
this will forbid everything

00:36:26.326 --> 00:36:28.874
that should be forbidden and
allow everything that should be

00:36:28.874 --> 00:36:32.555
allowed.
So, let me start with the most

00:36:32.555 --> 00:36:34.985
obvious formulation.
Mr.

00:36:34.985 --> 00:36:38.703
Carnot's version of the Second
Law was that you cannot have a

00:36:38.703 --> 00:36:42.296
process in which some heat
Q goes from a hot body to

00:36:42.296 --> 00:36:45.694
a cold body.
I'm sorry this allowed,

00:36:45.694 --> 00:36:50.690
right, according to Carnot,
this is not allowed.

00:36:54.900 --> 00:36:59.059
Right, heat can flow downhill,
cannot flow up hill.

00:36:59.059 --> 00:37:03.050
Let's see the entropy change
the universe with the two cases.

00:37:03.050 --> 00:37:05.505
In this case,
with this guy,

00:37:05.505 --> 00:37:10.781
the change in entropy is the
following: the upper reservoir

00:37:10.781 --> 00:37:15.175
lost some amount Q,
so ∆Q is a negative

00:37:15.175 --> 00:37:18.210
number, add some temperature
T_1,

00:37:18.210 --> 00:37:22.592
the lower reservoir gained
Q at temperature

00:37:22.592 --> 00:37:26.308
T_2.
Now, what's the overall sign of

00:37:26.308 --> 00:37:27.860
this?
Think about it.

00:37:27.860 --> 00:37:30.245
T_1 is bigger
than T_2,

00:37:30.245 --> 00:37:32.461
so this negative number is
smaller than this positive

00:37:32.461 --> 00:37:34.400
number,
so the whole thing is positive.

00:37:34.400 --> 00:37:39.079
That means it's allowed;
it's okay.

00:37:39.079 --> 00:37:41.790
By the same token,
if you take this process when

00:37:41.790 --> 00:37:44.615
heat flows up hill,
then this reservoir loses some

00:37:44.615 --> 00:37:47.730
heat Q at temperature
T_2,

00:37:47.730 --> 00:37:50.517
the other one gains heat
Q at temperature

00:37:50.517 --> 00:37:53.482
T_1,
but this is clearly less than

00:37:53.482 --> 00:37:56.625
zero because this positive
number is smaller than this

00:37:56.625 --> 00:37:59.476
negative number.
So, there you have a very

00:37:59.476 --> 00:38:02.446
simple example where if heat
flows the wrong way,

00:38:02.446 --> 00:38:04.860
the entropy of the universe
goes up.

00:38:08.800 --> 00:38:11.607
And it's very simple,
it's only--it's because,

00:38:11.607 --> 00:38:15.288
it's true that the heat loss of
this guy is the heat gain of

00:38:15.288 --> 00:38:16.925
that guy,
that's the Law of the

00:38:16.925 --> 00:38:19.240
Conservation of Energy.
So, energy doesn't change,

00:38:19.240 --> 00:38:21.770
but entropy changes,
because for entropy it's not

00:38:21.770 --> 00:38:24.405
the heat transferred,
it's heat transferred divided

00:38:24.405 --> 00:38:27.252
by temperature.
Therefore, a heat loss at one

00:38:27.252 --> 00:38:30.034
temperature and a [equal]
heat gain at a lower

00:38:30.034 --> 00:38:33.309
temperature don't cancel when it
comes to entropy.

00:38:33.309 --> 00:38:35.449
In one case the entropy goes up
and is allowed;

00:38:35.449 --> 00:38:37.270
other case entropy goes down,
that's not allowed.

00:38:40.730 --> 00:38:43.735
Okay so let's try,
that's certainly one process

00:38:43.735 --> 00:38:47.459
that you know should not be
allowed, but it's forbidden by

00:38:47.459 --> 00:38:50.530
the Third Law,
by a computation of entropy.

00:38:50.530 --> 00:38:53.924
So, the reason when you put a
hot and cold body together,

00:38:53.924 --> 00:38:57.621
heat flows from the cold to the
hot--I'm sorry from the hot to

00:38:57.621 --> 00:38:59.362
the cold,
