Professor Ramamurti

00:47:27.265 --> 00:47:28.276
Shankar: No,
that is correct,

00:47:28.276 --> 00:47:29.730
but I'm saying this computation
of entropy.

00:47:29.730 --> 00:47:33.382
The one line calculation I did,
namely there is no heat inflow,

00:47:33.382 --> 00:47:36.209
the ∆Q = 0,
so ∆Q over T

00:47:36.209 --> 00:47:38.647
summed up is also zero.
That's not how you do the

00:47:38.647 --> 00:47:39.190
entropy change.

00:47:42.789 --> 00:47:45.030
Is there any condition I made
on computing?

00:47:45.030 --> 00:47:47.144
Yes.
Student: Well,

00:47:47.144 --> 00:47:49.142
uhm… there's a gas
[inaudible]

00:47:49.142 --> 00:47:52.237
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Wait in fact,

00:47:52.237 --> 00:47:55.706
here's the interesting thing.
What's going to be the

00:47:55.706 --> 00:47:58.550
temperature difference between
