You guys are thinking of the

00:48:59.195 --> 00:49:01.348
computer air,
where if you let it expand it

00:49:01.348 --> 00:49:03.757
cools down because that is
expanding against the

00:49:03.757 --> 00:49:06.863
atmospheric pressure.
This gas is expanding into a

00:49:06.863 --> 00:49:09.209
complete vacuum.
It's got no piston to push

00:49:09.209 --> 00:49:12.188
against, nothing from outside
pushing, so these two points are

00:49:12.188 --> 00:49:13.360
the same temperature.

00:49:16.650 --> 00:49:19.152
So, the correct answer,
maybe you didn't catch on,

00:49:19.152 --> 00:49:22.268
but I will tell you the correct
answer is: There is an entropy

00:49:22.268 --> 00:49:25.265
increase in this problem,
because the final state

00:49:25.265 --> 00:49:29.019
definitely has a well-defined
entropy you can calculate,

00:49:29.019 --> 00:49:30.639
because it's an equilibrium
state.

00:49:30.639 --> 00:49:34.036
Initial one has a well-defined
entropy, in between stages here,

00:49:34.036 --> 00:49:36.940
are not on the PV
diagram because they were not

00:49:36.940 --> 00:49:39.486
equilibrium states.
So in this experiment,

00:49:39.486 --> 00:49:42.467
the way to calculate the
entropy change is not to do

00:49:42.467 --> 00:49:46.150
∆Q over T as it
happened in this experiment.

00:49:46.150 --> 00:49:49.405
What you really want to say is
my gas was here in the

00:49:49.405 --> 00:49:51.909
beginning, my gas is there in
the end,

00:49:51.909 --> 00:49:54.447
both are states of equilibrium,
both have well-defined

00:49:54.447 --> 00:49:57.224
temperature and I can find the
entropy change in going from

00:49:57.224 --> 00:49:59.139
here to here for any process I
want.

00:49:59.139 --> 00:50:02.993
As long as that process keeps
the system near equilibrium,

00:50:02.993 --> 00:50:06.644
so I can follow dot by dot
where I'm moving and add the

00:50:06.644 --> 00:50:10.514
∆Q over Ts.
The correct rule for entropy

00:50:10.514 --> 00:50:14.379
change is ∆Q/T computed
on a path in which the system

00:50:14.379 --> 00:50:18.268
never strays from equilibrium.
Now, your system strayed from

00:50:18.268 --> 00:50:21.245
equilibrium all the time.
But we're not interested in how

00:50:21.245 --> 00:50:23.670
it got from here to here.
We are saying what's the

00:50:23.670 --> 00:50:25.909
entropy here and what's the
entropy here.

00:50:25.909 --> 00:50:28.682
Since this at the same
temperature, I know one way to

00:50:28.682 --> 00:50:31.614
go from there to there is to
follow the isotherm because

00:50:31.614 --> 00:50:34.920
that'll connect the two points
in this particular problem.

00:50:34.920 --> 00:50:38.402
Then I know the entropy change
is S_2 -

00:50:38.402 --> 00:50:41.952
S_1 is nR log
V_2 over

00:50:41.952 --> 00:50:43.660
V_1.

00:50:54.750 --> 00:50:57.960
So, here is the subtle point I
want to explain to you.

00:50:57.960 --> 00:51:00.235
This is worth understanding.
A lot of people do all the

00:51:00.235 --> 00:51:02.879
problems and get everything
right, but don't appreciate this

00:51:02.879 --> 00:51:05.897
particular question.
The free expansion of a gas

00:51:05.897 --> 00:51:10.313
into a vacuum takes it from one
equilibrium state called 1 to

00:51:10.313 --> 00:51:13.110
another equilibrium state called
2.

00:51:13.110 --> 00:51:16.445
In the actual expansion,
the system went through a stage

00:51:16.445 --> 00:51:19.719
which cannot be even shown in
the PV diagram,

00:51:19.719 --> 00:51:22.064
they were not equilibrium
states, they didn't have well

00:51:22.064 --> 00:51:23.845
defined pressure,
didn't have well defined

00:51:23.845 --> 00:51:25.903
temperature.
How do you find a temperature

00:51:25.903 --> 00:51:27.964
when half the box is empty?
Doesn't have it,

00:51:27.964 --> 00:51:30.150
you cannot it T
temperature of the gas.

00:51:30.150 --> 00:51:32.280
So, what do you mean by
∆Q over T,

00:51:32.280 --> 00:51:34.519
there is no T.
Only when it settles down,

00:51:34.519 --> 00:51:37.310
there is a T.
Every settled down equilibrium

00:51:37.310 --> 00:51:40.520
state is a well-defined entropy.
What we're trying to do is to

00:51:40.520 --> 00:51:43.226
compute that difference.
The way to compute the

00:51:43.226 --> 00:51:47.317
difference is to forget about
what actually happened and

00:51:47.317 --> 00:51:52.778
instead do the following.
Take the gas like that and turn

00:51:52.778 --> 00:51:56.265
it this way, [90 degree
rotation]

00:51:56.265 --> 00:51:59.434
if you like.
Just for convenience,

00:51:59.434 --> 00:52:02.284
put a piston there at the
halfway point,

00:52:02.284 --> 00:52:06.815
put some weights on it so that
the pressure equals the pressure

00:52:06.815 --> 00:52:10.250
inside and slowly remove little
by little,

00:52:10.250 --> 00:52:13.183
and keeping it on a reservoir a
temperature

00:52:13.183 --> 00:52:16.347
T_1.
Which is the temperature at

00:52:16.347 --> 00:52:19.117
which all of this happens,
or at some temperature

00:52:19.117 --> 00:52:21.993
T.
As you remove the grain of

00:52:21.993 --> 00:52:25.856
sand, what happens is the gas
gets some energy,

00:52:25.856 --> 00:52:30.560
that's the ∆Q over
T, the reservoir loses

00:52:30.560 --> 00:52:33.800
some heat;
in fact, the reservoir loses

00:52:33.800 --> 00:52:37.052
the same amount of heat
∆Q at the same

00:52:37.052 --> 00:52:40.565
temperature T.
So in fact, what happens in

00:52:40.565 --> 00:52:44.870
this process is entropy of the
universe does not change at all.

00:52:44.870 --> 00:52:48.932
The entropy gain of the gas;
this is an entropy loss of the

00:52:48.932 --> 00:52:51.699
reservoir.
But I used this as a device for

00:52:51.699 --> 00:52:55.440
finding the entropy gain of the
gas in the other process.

00:53:00.679 --> 00:53:06.222
So, this is the part that is
absolutely central to this whole

00:53:06.222 --> 00:53:09.639
argument how entropy is
calculated.

00:53:09.639 --> 00:53:13.165
In a real spontaneous expansion
of a gas, where there was no

00:53:13.165 --> 00:53:16.320
reservoir, no nothing,
we just broke the partition and

00:53:16.320 --> 00:53:18.540
expanded, there is a change in
entropy.

00:53:18.540 --> 00:53:22.929
That's an irreversible process.
But to find the change in

00:53:22.929 --> 00:53:26.690
entropy in this problem,
since 1 and 2 have well-defined

00:53:26.690 --> 00:53:29.710
entropies,
we can find the change between

00:53:29.710 --> 00:53:33.757
1 and 2 by going to a different
experiment in which it was

00:53:33.757 --> 00:53:36.749
brought from 1 to 2,
not in this crazy irreversible

00:53:36.749 --> 00:53:39.196
way, but by putting it in
contact with the heat bath at

00:53:39.196 --> 00:53:42.013
that temperature T,
removing grain after grain,

00:53:42.013 --> 00:53:45.074
never straying far from
equilibrium, that's when we find

00:53:45.074 --> 00:53:47.671
this change.
So, you replace the dotted

00:53:47.671 --> 00:53:51.804
line, where you cannot compute
anything, by a solid line where

00:53:51.804 --> 00:53:54.211
you can.
But since the change in entropy

00:53:54.211 --> 00:53:56.944
between 1 and 2 doesn't depend
on how you got there,

00:53:56.944 --> 00:53:59.123
that's the answer.
But this process,

00:53:59.123 --> 00:54:02.842
where you can actually see it
is the one in which ∆S

00:54:02.842 --> 00:54:05.260
of the universe is actually at
zero.

00:54:05.260 --> 00:54:07.573
Why?
Because you are putting in

00:54:07.573 --> 00:54:10.320
contact with the reservoir at
the same temperature,

00:54:10.320 --> 00:54:13.698
so ∆Q over T
for the gas and ∆Q over

00:54:13.698 --> 00:54:16.851
T for the reservoir
exactly cancel because they're

00:54:16.851 --> 00:54:19.948
at the same temperature and
∆Q for one is minus

00:54:19.948 --> 00:54:24.972
∆Q for the other.
So, don't confuse the two

00:54:24.972 --> 00:54:28.077
processes.
One is a reversible process in

00:54:28.077 --> 00:54:31.678
which a gas is slowly allowed to
expand from the initial state of

00:54:31.678 --> 00:54:34.604
the final stage by removing
grain after grain of some

00:54:34.604 --> 00:54:38.205
externally applied pressure in a
process where the entropy of the

00:54:38.205 --> 00:54:41.672
universe doesn't change,
gas and reservoir change by

00:54:41.672 --> 00:54:44.022
equal amounts.
But the punch line is I don't

00:54:44.022 --> 00:54:46.999
care what happens in reservoir,
I want to know how much the gas

00:54:46.999 --> 00:54:49.132
gained,
because that is the gain I need

00:54:49.132 --> 00:54:51.903
to find S_2 -
S_1 for this

00:54:51.903 --> 00:54:54.837
process.
So, this is how we always find

00:54:54.837 --> 00:54:57.822
entropy change.
In real life processes happen

00:54:57.822 --> 00:55:00.869
in a way in which entropy of the
universe goes up.

00:55:00.869 --> 00:55:03.864
Because take this box,
in the real experiment,

00:55:03.864 --> 00:55:07.989
remember there is no reservoir,
there's only the box of gas.

00:55:07.989 --> 00:55:09.827
It expanded,
its entropy went up,

00:55:09.827 --> 00:55:12.470
so entropy of the universe
actually went up.

00:55:12.470 --> 00:55:18.391
That's why it's allowed.
The entropy of the universe

00:55:18.391 --> 00:55:22.436
went up by an amount equal to
the increase in entropy of the

00:55:22.436 --> 00:55:26.545
gas when it goes from 1 to 2.
To find the increase in entropy

00:55:26.545 --> 00:55:30.314
of the gas when it goes from 1
to 2, I create a second process

00:55:30.314 --> 00:55:33.651
in which I can compute the
change by letting it go in a

00:55:33.651 --> 00:55:37.050
sequence of connected dots and
finding the change.

00:55:37.050 --> 00:55:40.840
So, the way you use to find the
change in entropy is not the way

00:55:40.840 --> 00:55:44.090
the entropy increase took place
in the real process.

00:55:44.090 --> 00:55:46.245
So, I don't think I want to
repeat it anymore,

00:55:46.245 --> 00:55:49.118
but it's an important point and
you should really think about

00:55:49.118 --> 00:55:53.034
that.
Alright, now the last point is,

00:55:53.034 --> 00:55:59.778
what does--Let's analyze this
final formula I got for entropy

00:55:59.778 --> 00:56:04.050
change for free expansion of a
gas.

00:56:07.730 --> 00:56:12.614
Let's take a simple case where
the gas expanded from some

00:56:12.614 --> 00:56:16.539
volume V to volume 2
times V.

00:56:16.539 --> 00:56:19.530
What is S_2 -
S_1?

00:56:19.530 --> 00:56:25.041
S_2 -
S_1 = nR

00:56:25.041 --> 00:56:27.601
log 2.
2 happens to be

00:56:27.601 --> 00:56:30.120
V_2/V
_1;

00:56:30.120 --> 00:56:34.781
the volume is doubled.
Let me re-write this as Nk

00:56:34.781 --> 00:56:40.930
log 2, because the number of
moles times R is the

00:56:40.930 --> 00:56:44.889
number of molecules times
k.

00:56:44.889 --> 00:56:49.626
Let me re-write that as log of
2 to the N times

00:56:49.626 --> 00:56:50.610
k.

00:56:55.679 --> 00:57:02.400
Now, I will tell you what all
these factors mean and that

00:57:02.400 --> 00:57:07.432
comes from the following.
Thermodynamics only told you

00:57:07.432 --> 00:57:10.634
the formula for the change in
the entropy of a gas,

00:57:10.634 --> 00:57:13.579
didn't tell you what the
entropy itself is.

00:57:13.579 --> 00:57:17.524
So, the formula for the entropy
of a gas, without talking about

00:57:17.524 --> 00:57:21.532
the change and also this formula
∆S is ∆Q over

00:57:21.532 --> 00:57:23.699
T,
doesn't even believe in atoms.

00:57:23.699 --> 00:57:25.363
You don't need atoms,
you don't need molecules,

00:57:25.363 --> 00:57:27.280
you don't need to know what
anything is made up of.

00:57:27.280 --> 00:57:30.760
In fact, it was discovered long
before atoms were proven to

00:57:30.760 --> 00:57:33.948
exist.
Boltzmann is the guy who gave

00:57:33.948 --> 00:57:39.924
the formula for what the entropy
of a gas is in terms of what the

00:57:39.924 --> 00:57:44.939
individual molecules are doing.
That's the punch line of what's

00:57:44.939 --> 00:57:48.498
called statistical mechanics,
which gives you the microscopic

00:57:48.498 --> 00:57:51.743
origin of thermodynamics.
Thermodynamics to this stage

00:57:51.743 --> 00:57:55.363
talk about fluids and solids and
gases and nothing there requires

00:57:55.363 --> 00:57:57.570
that everything be made up of
atoms,

00:57:57.570 --> 00:57:59.250
you don't have to know what
it's made of.

00:57:59.250 --> 00:58:02.789
But if you tell me it's made up
of atoms, you have a better idea

00:58:02.789 --> 00:58:05.935
of what entropy means and here
is Boltzmann's formula for

00:58:05.935 --> 00:58:08.610
entropy.
I am going to write it down.

00:58:08.610 --> 00:58:14.739
Boltzmann constant times log
Ω.

00:58:14.739 --> 00:58:16.769
I'll tell you what omega is in
a minute.

00:58:16.769 --> 00:58:20.401
This is such an important
formula it is written in

00:58:20.401 --> 00:58:23.436
Boltzmann's tombstone.
So, when physicists go to

00:58:23.436 --> 00:58:26.050
Vienna, we skip the orchestras
and everything else,

00:58:26.050 --> 00:58:29.970
we go to Boltzmann's tomb and
we read this formula once more

00:58:29.970 --> 00:58:33.161
with some passion.
That's a summary of a lifetime

00:58:33.161 --> 00:58:35.007
of work.
But it's a great formula and

00:58:35.007 --> 00:58:37.675
you will understand once you
know the formula what all this

00:58:37.675 --> 00:58:41.162
means.
So, let me tell you what omega

00:58:41.162 --> 00:58:42.876
means.
I am going to say it in words

00:58:42.876 --> 00:58:44.559
and then I am going to apply it
to this problem.

00:58:44.559 --> 00:58:47.822
If you took any gas,
let it be under certain

00:58:47.822 --> 00:58:52.146
conditions that macroscopically
has some pressure and some

00:58:52.146 --> 00:58:56.570
volume and so on.
So, here is the gas at one

00:58:56.570 --> 00:58:58.829
instant;
now we believe in atoms,

00:58:58.829 --> 00:59:01.550
here are these atoms scattered
all over the place.

00:59:05.260 --> 00:59:11.420
Suppose I wait a little bit,
what did the gas look like?

00:59:11.420 --> 00:59:14.970
It looks like that.
If you can see every atom,

00:59:14.970 --> 00:59:18.449
the atomic configuration has
changed.

00:59:18.449 --> 00:59:21.730
But macroscopically nothing has
changed.

00:59:21.730 --> 00:59:24.742
Instead of atom A being
here, maybe A has gone

00:59:24.742 --> 00:59:26.530
there and B has come
here.

00:59:26.530 --> 00:59:28.815
In particular,
if you divide the volume into

00:59:28.815 --> 00:59:31.420
some number of little cells that
you can count,

00:59:31.420 --> 00:59:35.255
on the average the gas' uniform
density, there are some number

00:59:35.255 --> 00:59:38.210
of atoms, per every little cube
you can form,

00:59:38.210 --> 00:59:42.030
a little later I move on and
somebody else moves in.

00:59:42.030 --> 00:59:44.130
Macroscopically,
it looks the same to me.

00:59:44.130 --> 00:59:46.010
Microscopically,
stuff is going on.

00:59:46.010 --> 00:59:51.099
Omega is the number of
different microscopic

00:59:51.099 --> 00:59:58.199
arrangements that agree with
what is seen macroscopically.

00:59:58.199 --> 01:00:00.238
When I say microscopic
arrangements,

01:00:00.238 --> 01:00:03.442
I really mean the following:
give every molecule a name,

01:00:03.442 --> 01:00:05.656
A, B,
C, D,

01:00:05.656 --> 01:00:07.777
whatever.
Then put A here and

01:00:07.777 --> 01:00:09.697
B here,
C here and D

01:00:09.697 --> 01:00:11.690
there;
that's one arrangement.

01:00:11.690 --> 01:00:13.349
Then permute them,
put D here and B

01:00:13.349 --> 01:00:14.767
here and C here and
A there,

01:00:14.767 --> 01:00:16.981
that's another arrangement.
To my naked eye they,

01:00:16.981 --> 01:00:19.535
all look the same,
but they all produce the same

01:00:19.535 --> 01:00:21.709
macroscopic effect,
but they're different

01:00:21.709 --> 01:00:25.633
microscopic arrangements.
And you're supposed to take the

01:00:25.633 --> 01:00:29.702
log of the number of these
arrangements multiply by this

01:00:29.702 --> 01:00:32.214
constant,
called Boltzmann's constant,

01:00:32.214 --> 01:00:34.130
to get the entropy of the
state.

01:00:34.130 --> 01:00:37.180
So, now let's apply it to this
gas here.

01:00:40.639 --> 01:00:43.608
Now, the number of microscopic
arrangements,

01:00:43.608 --> 01:00:46.300
if you really want to get down
to it,

01:00:46.300 --> 01:00:49.079
requires dividing the box into
tiny little cells,

01:00:49.079 --> 01:00:52.323
maybe 1 cubic millimeter and
saying how many atoms are in

01:00:52.323 --> 01:00:54.769
each region.
But we're going to do a crude

01:00:54.769 --> 01:00:57.336
calculation in which we'll only
say the following:

01:00:57.336 --> 01:01:00.480
that either a molecule is on
the left or is on the right.

01:01:00.480 --> 01:01:04.623
We are saying these are the
only two positions open to the

01:01:04.623 --> 01:01:06.280
gas;
left or right.

01:01:06.280 --> 01:01:08.715
Of course, in the left,
there is left corner top and

01:01:08.715 --> 01:01:10.960
left corner bottom,
but don't worry about it.

01:01:10.960 --> 01:01:13.681
Just say that only two things
it can do, it can be on the left

01:01:13.681 --> 01:01:18.393
or it can be on the right.
Now, let's ask ourselves if the

01:01:18.393 --> 01:01:20.740
gas looks like this.

01:01:25.170 --> 01:01:29.750
How many ways can it be in this
arrangement?

01:01:29.750 --> 01:01:34.620
As compared to how many ways it
can be in this arrangement?

01:01:40.530 --> 01:01:44.352
It is like the following:
molecules are moving randomly,

01:01:44.352 --> 01:01:48.521
a given molecule has got 50/50
chance of being on the left or

01:01:48.521 --> 01:01:51.943
being on the right.
You are demanding that all the

01:01:51.943 --> 01:01:55.407
N molecules on their own,
there's no partition now,

01:01:55.407 --> 01:01:57.900
on their own be on the
left-hand side.

01:01:57.900 --> 01:02:03.755
You can see it's like tossing a
coin N times and wanting

01:02:03.755 --> 01:02:07.688
heads every time.
Because you want every guy in a

01:02:07.688 --> 01:02:10.380
random process to end up picking
left.

01:02:10.380 --> 01:02:14.046
So, if you want them all to be
left, there's only one way to do

01:02:14.046 --> 01:02:17.179
that, and that's like saying I
tossed a million coins,

01:02:17.179 --> 01:02:20.530
I wanted all heads.
There's only one way to do that.

01:02:20.530 --> 01:02:23.148
So, that arrangement,
if you like,

01:02:23.148 --> 01:02:26.719
we will say looks like this,
left, left, left,

01:02:26.719 --> 01:02:28.968
left, left;
for everybody,

01:02:28.968 --> 01:02:33.902
that's the arrangement here.
Take another one where one

01:02:33.902 --> 01:02:39.386
molecule is over here,
and all the others are here on

01:02:39.386 --> 01:02:43.012
the left side.
That looks like left,

01:02:43.012 --> 01:02:46.240
left, left, right,
left, left, left.

01:02:46.240 --> 01:02:50.491
But that's one arrangement.
But have I done my complete

01:02:50.491 --> 01:02:52.740
homework here?
Are there more arrangements?

01:02:52.740 --> 01:02:55.374
I want you to think about it.
Student: [inaudible]

01:02:55.374 --> 01:02:57.782
arrangements Professor
Ramamurti Shankar: Pardon

01:02:57.782 --> 01:02:59.261
me.
Student: [inaudible]

01:02:59.261 --> 01:03:00.432
arrangements.
Professor Ramamurti

01:03:00.432 --> 01:03:01.813
Shankar: This is only one of
the arrangements for the

01:03:01.813 --> 01:03:04.586
molecule on the right.
There's another arrangement in

01:03:04.586 --> 01:03:08.826
which I can have the second
molecule, molecule Moe or Joe or

01:03:08.826 --> 01:03:11.987
Poe, whoever's here.
You can pick them in N

01:03:11.987 --> 01:03:13.746
ways.
Already when one is on the left

01:03:13.746 --> 01:03:16.453
and N - 1 on the right,
there are more ways in which

01:03:16.453 --> 01:03:18.721
that can happen.
So, your eye sees one on the

01:03:18.721 --> 01:03:21.522
right, N - 1 on the left.
There are N ways in

01:03:21.522 --> 01:03:25.159
which that can happen.
It's like saying if I toss

01:03:25.159 --> 01:03:28.659
coins, I want 1 head and 99
tails.

01:03:28.659 --> 01:03:33.357
Well, it turns out there are a
100 ways in which it can happen,

01:03:33.357 --> 01:03:37.525
because the one head I got
could have occurred in one of

01:03:37.525 --> 01:03:42.877
the hundred different turns.
Now, suppose I want 2 heads and

01:03:42.877 --> 01:03:48.543
98 tails, then as you know the
way to do that is 100 times 99

01:03:48.543 --> 01:03:52.095
divided by 1 times 2.
These are some combinatorics

01:03:52.095 --> 01:03:56.586
you learn in high school.
So, you find that if you plot

01:03:56.586 --> 01:04:02.838
number heads over the total
number, and ask for how many

01:04:02.838 --> 01:04:08.806
ways in which that can happen,
all heads can occur in only

01:04:08.806 --> 01:04:12.335
way, every coin has to be head,
1 head less,

01:04:12.335 --> 01:04:16.440
1 tail and 99 heads can occur
in N ways,

01:04:16.440 --> 01:04:18.409
then it'll become more and more
and more.

01:04:18.409 --> 01:04:21.922
And you will find the 50/50
chance of half the number of

01:04:21.922 --> 01:04:25.755
heads and half the number of
tails has the biggest occurrence

01:04:25.755 --> 01:04:26.330
rate,

01:04:30.280 --> 01:04:33.316
because that's the most number
of ways to get 50/50 than

01:04:33.316 --> 01:04:36.916
anything else.
And 100 heads is as bad as 100

01:04:36.916 --> 01:04:38.658
tails.
Again, there's only one way in

01:04:38.658 --> 01:04:40.839
which you can get all heads in
one way and which you can get

01:04:40.839 --> 01:04:42.639
all tails.
But as you start scrambling

01:04:42.639 --> 01:04:44.349
them there are more and more
ways.

01:04:44.349 --> 01:04:48.960
That means for the molecule,
if you have a 100 molecules,

01:04:48.960 --> 01:04:53.652
the number of states omega is
largest when they're equally

01:04:53.652 --> 01:04:56.492
distributed.
In fact, as the number

01:04:56.492 --> 01:05:00.300
molecules goes from 100 to 1000
to million to 10^(23),

01:05:00.300 --> 01:05:04.246
this function is so sharply
peaked that the approximate

01:05:04.246 --> 01:05:07.900
formula for omega,
when it's at the 50/50 thing,

01:05:07.900 --> 01:05:11.538
is in fact 2 to the N.
Namely, all the arrangements

01:05:11.538 --> 01:05:14.530
more or less belong to this
configuration.

01:05:14.530 --> 01:05:18.496
Therefore, if you go back to
the Boltzmann formula and,

01:05:18.496 --> 01:05:21.139
wait let me keep the formula
here,

01:05:21.139 --> 01:05:25.307
and look at S = K log
Ω, then you find

01:05:25.307 --> 01:05:30.380
S_1 is when
everybody is on the left,

01:05:30.380 --> 01:05:35.777
that is k log 1,
and S_2 is

01:05:35.777 --> 01:05:41.389
50/50 mix, half on the left and
half on the right,

01:05:41.389 --> 01:05:46.260
that entropy is k log
2^(N),.

01:05:46.260 --> 01:05:49.990
Therefore, you can see that's
what I wrote down here,

01:05:49.990 --> 01:05:52.000
K log 2^(N).

01:05:57.199 --> 01:06:01.690
So, the way to understand
entropy is the following.

01:06:01.690 --> 01:06:07.954
If I give you a gas and ask,
"Will they ever like to be in

01:06:07.954 --> 01:06:12.460
the left half of the box on
their own?"

01:06:12.460 --> 01:06:14.773
Of course they won't.
But if you start them out that

01:06:14.773 --> 01:06:17.510
way, you force them to be on the
left they'll be on the left.

01:06:17.510 --> 01:06:20.326
The question is if you remove
the partition,

01:06:20.326 --> 01:06:22.785
what would they likely do?
Unlike coins,

01:06:22.785 --> 01:06:25.527
which once they land on the
head, they have to stay on the

01:06:25.527 --> 01:06:27.500
head, these molecules can move
around.

01:06:27.500 --> 01:06:30.452
The question is if they were
all left to begin with,

01:06:30.452 --> 01:06:32.420
how long can they possibly
last?

01:06:32.420 --> 01:06:36.137
If they start moving randomly,
they will always end up doing

01:06:36.137 --> 01:06:39.539
this because there are many,
many more ways to do this,

01:06:39.539 --> 01:06:40.800
than to do this.

01:06:44.050 --> 01:06:47.226
So, things go from one
arrangement, macroscopic to

01:06:47.226 --> 01:06:49.820
another one, left to their own
device,

01:06:49.820 --> 01:06:53.650
because the final state can be
realized in many,

01:06:53.650 --> 01:06:56.909
many more ways than the initial
state.

01:06:56.909 --> 01:07:02.089
Similarly, if you combine a hot
gas and cold gas--This is hot

01:07:02.089 --> 01:07:05.355
and this is cold,
with a thermally insulating

01:07:05.355 --> 01:07:09.026
partition, then all the hots are
on the left and all the colds

01:07:09.026 --> 01:07:11.483
are on the right.
If you remove the thermal

01:07:11.483 --> 01:07:14.240
insulation, but not even remove
it, just replace it by a

01:07:14.240 --> 01:07:16.697
heat-conducting thing,
eventually the temperatures

01:07:16.697 --> 01:07:19.552
would equalize.
So, what you find every time

01:07:19.552 --> 01:07:22.727
is, there's many,
many ways in which you can pack

01:07:22.727 --> 01:07:26.829
your atoms--if you put all the
hot on the left and all the cold

01:07:26.829 --> 01:07:29.136
on the right,
that can be achieved in fewer

01:07:29.136 --> 01:07:31.176
ways than in which you let them
go wherever they like.

01:07:31.176 --> 01:07:33.178
[He should have said,
"If you put all hot ones on one

01:07:33.178 --> 01:07:34.819
side and cold on the other,
there are fewer ways of doing

01:07:34.819 --> 01:07:35.525
that, than if you let them go
wherever they liked"]

01:07:35.525 --> 01:07:37.632
So,
what you find is entropy is the

01:07:37.632 --> 01:07:40.829
direct measure of how disordered
your system is.

01:07:40.829 --> 01:07:44.498
One technical measure of
disorder is to ask how many

01:07:44.498 --> 01:07:47.880
microscopic arrangements can
lead to what I see,

01:07:47.880 --> 01:07:50.469
and take the log of that
number.

01:07:50.469 --> 01:07:53.920
And what you find is this has a
very low entropy;

01:07:53.920 --> 01:07:57.496
this is a very high entropy.
Because this configuration--In

01:07:57.496 --> 01:08:00.748
other words, if you took a gas
in a whole room and asked will

01:08:00.748 --> 01:08:02.699
it ever go to this
configuration,

01:08:02.699 --> 01:08:06.059
there is a slight chance it
will.

01:08:06.059 --> 01:08:08.456
That chance is one part and
2^(N),

01:08:08.456 --> 01:08:11.512
where N is 10^(23),
so it's not something you

01:08:11.512 --> 01:08:13.849
should wait for,
but it can happen.

01:08:13.849 --> 01:08:17.068
So, the Second Law of
Thermodynamics is a statistical

01:08:17.068 --> 01:08:18.496
law.
Microscopically,

01:08:18.496 --> 01:08:22.458
it's perfectly allowed for a
gas, for suddenly all the gas in

01:08:22.458 --> 01:08:25.100
the whole room to come to where
I am.

01:08:25.100 --> 01:08:28.123
It's allowed but you don't hold
your breath, because that's not

01:08:28.123 --> 01:08:30.722
likely to happen.
The odds for that is again one

01:08:30.722 --> 01:08:32.840
part in 1 over 2 to some huge
number.

01:08:32.840 --> 01:08:35.095
On the other hand,
if in this part of the room we

01:08:35.095 --> 01:08:37.303
release some gas,
it'll very quickly spread out,

01:08:37.303 --> 01:08:39.229
because there are more ways to
do it.

01:08:39.229 --> 01:08:44.489
So, we understand completely
now why certain things occur and

01:08:44.489 --> 01:08:47.912
why they don't.
Because if you took hot water

01:08:47.912 --> 01:08:50.977
and cold water,
you are separating them to fast

01:08:50.977 --> 01:08:54.493
molecules and slow molecules,
as long as they're in different

01:08:54.493 --> 01:08:56.770
insulated containers,
that's the best they can do.

01:08:56.770 --> 01:08:59.708
But if you put them in contact,
so that they no longer have to

01:08:59.708 --> 01:09:01.538
be separated,
the question is will they

01:09:01.538 --> 01:09:04.019
remain separated.
It's like saying I have bunch

01:09:04.019 --> 01:09:07.109
of coins which are all left and
all right, but they're allowed

01:09:07.109 --> 01:09:10.173
to flip as a function time,
but they'll never remain that

01:09:10.173 --> 01:09:12.004
way.
Okay, so what'll happen is the

01:09:12.004 --> 01:09:14.976
cold molecules and hot will
mingle, and soon the container

01:09:14.976 --> 01:09:18.104
will have cold everywhere and
hot everywhere and you will get

01:09:18.104 --> 01:09:21.432
some intermediate temperature.
Or if you took two different

01:09:21.432 --> 01:09:24.437
dyes, you know water here,
on top of it you pour some red

01:09:24.437 --> 01:09:26.458
paint,
they'll be initially separated

01:09:26.458 --> 01:09:29.381
after a while they will mix,
because there's no reason for

01:09:29.381 --> 01:09:32.510
the hot--for the red molecules
to stay on the top forever;

01:09:32.510 --> 01:09:35.132
they would like to occupy the
whole box and so would the

01:09:35.132 --> 01:09:37.230
colorless ones,
and eventually it will become

01:09:37.230 --> 01:09:39.479
pink.
Because there's more ways to

01:09:39.479 --> 01:09:41.949
remain pink than to remain
separated.

01:09:41.949 --> 01:09:45.541
Likewise, if pink spontaneously
separated into red and

01:09:45.541 --> 01:09:48.251
colorless, that is very,
very improbable,

01:09:48.251 --> 01:09:51.640
because entropy for that state
would be lower.

01:09:51.640 --> 01:09:55.391
So, you have to understand the
Second Law of Thermodynamics is

01:09:55.391 --> 01:09:58.589
saying certain things occur
because if you go in that

01:09:58.589 --> 01:10:02.279
direction you can realize that
arrangement in more ways.

01:10:02.279 --> 01:10:06.811
And since microscopic motion is
random, it's like tossing coins

01:10:06.811 --> 01:10:10.319
to ask for N heads many
thousand times;

01:10:10.319 --> 01:10:12.782
it's like asking all the
molecules to be on the left side

01:10:12.782 --> 01:10:14.850
of the room, to ask for 50/50
head and tails,

01:10:14.850 --> 01:10:18.520
is like asking for molecules to
populate the room equally.

01:10:18.520 --> 01:10:21.520
Okay, so that's called the
arrow of time.

01:10:21.520 --> 01:10:23.539
But you've got to be careful
about one thing;

01:10:23.539 --> 01:10:26.479
the entropy of a part of the
universe can go down.

01:10:26.479 --> 01:10:29.859
It's just the entropy of the
whole universe will not go down.

01:10:29.859 --> 01:10:33.675
So, all of life is an example
of lowering entropy because,

01:10:33.675 --> 01:10:37.757
you know, the creation of life
or the creation of tomatoes out

01:10:37.757 --> 01:10:41.773
of mud is a highly organizing
process so the entropy there is

01:10:41.773 --> 01:10:44.741
really going down.
